                <head>203. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>In Special National Intelligence Estimate 58-5/1-62, “Communist Reactions to
                    Additional US Courses of Action in Laos and North Vietnam,” issued June 12,
                    1962, the intelligence community predicted increased Soviet and Chinese
                    materiel, arms, and political support for North Vietnam if the United States
                    attacked supply bases in Laos or launched either air attacks or amphibious
                    action against North Vietnam. For text, see <ref target="frus1961-63v02#pg_445">
                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1961–1963, volume II, pages
                        445</ref>–<ref target="frus1961-63v02#pg_447">447</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
